{"word":"H7301 - רָוָה - râvâh - raw-vaw' - Bathe","slug":"H7301","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">רָוָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>râvâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>raw-vaw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bathe"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E8;&#x05D5;&#x05D4; - ra&#x0302;va&#x0302;h</b> - <i>raw-vaw'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>slake</i> the thirst (occasionally of other appetites): - bathe, make drunk, (take the) fill, satiate, (abundantly) satisfy, soak, water (abundantly)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7302\">H7302</a>, <a href=\"#/H7310\">H7310</a>, <a href=\"#/H7377\">H7377</a>"}]}